{
  "texts": [
    "Additionally, in realworld speech scenarios, factors such as environmental noise, the speaker's emotions, variations in speech rate, and other conditions will also influence recognition performance, which poses higher requirements on the robustness of the models.",
    "Therefore, improving the robustness of the model and effectively handling small-scale dialect corpora have become critical challenges in the field of Chinese DSR.",
    "(5) Updates of Language Models: The language model plays a vital role in Chinese DSR (Ren et al. 2019).",
    "These models not only provide grammatical and lexical support for speech recognition but also enhance the system's ability to comprehend and transcribe dialect content accurately.",
    "However, the study of language habits and vocabulary usage in specific dialects still faces some challenges."
  ]
}